Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of search engine technology in improving online public access catalogs (OPACs) in libraries. This topic falls under the field of information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The paper also discusses user-centered design and user intentions, which are relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper mentions ranking criteria and sophisticated results presentations, which are related to database systems (cs.DB).
